API docs by Redocly

Wsf Fares API (1.0.0)

Download OpenAPI specification:

Wsf Fares API - Washington State Department of Transportation APIs

cache-flush-date-fares

Cache invalidation timestamp for static WSF fares data.

Get cache flush timestamp for static fares data.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/cacheflushdate

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie } from 'ws-dottie';
import { fetchCacheFlushDateFares } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-fares/core';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: fetchCacheFlushDateFares,
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API

"2025-11-14T19:42:45.737Z"

List valid departing terminals for a trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchTerminalFaresInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format; must be within valid date range from GetValidDateRange.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/terminals/{TripDate}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie } from 'ws-dottie';
import { fetchTerminalFares } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-fares/core';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: fetchTerminalFares,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-16"
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 19 total)

[
  • {
    • "TerminalID": 1,
    • "Description": "Anacortes"
    }
]

List arriving terminals for a given departing terminal and trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchTerminalMatesFaresInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format; must be within valid date range from GetValidDateRange.

TerminalID
required
number (FetchTerminalMatesFaresInputTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the departing terminal.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/terminalMates/{TripDate}/{TerminalID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie } from 'ws-dottie';
import { fetchTerminalMatesFares } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-fares/core';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: fetchTerminalMatesFares,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-16",
    "TerminalID": 1
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 4 total)

[
  • {
    • "TerminalID": 10,
    • "Description": "Friday Harbor"
    }
]

valid-date-range

Validity period for published WSF fare data.

Get the validity date range for published fares data.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/validdaterange

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie } from 'ws-dottie';

  endpoint: fetchFaresValidDateRange,
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

terminals

WSF terminal facilities serving as departure and arrival points for ferry routes.

List all fare line items for a specific terminal combination and trip type.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchFareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminalsInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Must be within valid date range.

DepartingTerminalID
required
number (FetchFareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminalsInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the departing terminal.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (FetchFareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminalsInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the arriving terminal.

RoundTrip
required
boolean (FetchFareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminalsInputRoundTripParam)

True for round trip fares, false for one-way fares.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/fareLineItems/{TripDate}/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}/{RoundTrip}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie } from 'ws-dottie';
import { fetchFareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminals } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-fares/core';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: fetchFareLineItemsByTripDateAndTerminals,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-16",
    "DepartingTerminalID": 3,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 7,
    "RoundTrip": false
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 23 total)

[
  • {
    • "FareLineItemID": 1,
    • "FareLineItem": "Adult (age 19 - 64)",
    • "Category": "Passenger",
    • "DirectionIndependent": false,
    • "Amount": 0
    }
]

terminal-combo

Valid terminal pairings with fare collection procedures for WSF routes.

Get fare collection description for a specific terminal combination and trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchTerminalComboFaresInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Must be within valid date range.

DepartingTerminalID
required
number (FetchTerminalComboFaresInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the departing terminal.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (FetchTerminalComboFaresInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the arriving terminal.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/terminalCombo/{TripDate}/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie } from 'ws-dottie';
import { fetchTerminalComboFares } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-fares/core';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: fetchTerminalComboFares,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-16",
    "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 10
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API

{
  • "DepartingDescription": "Anacortes",
  • "ArrivingDescription": "Friday Harbor",
  • "CollectionDescription": "Passenger and vehicle/driver fares are collected at Anacortes, while no fares are collected at Friday Harbor."
}

fare-line-items

Individual fare components for WSF routes by passenger and vehicle types.

List popular fare line items for a terminal combination.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchFareLineItemsBasicInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Must be within valid date range.

DepartingTerminalID
required
number (FetchFareLineItemsBasicInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the departing terminal.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (FetchFareLineItemsBasicInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the arriving terminal.

RoundTrip
required
boolean (FetchFareLineItemsBasicInputRoundTripParam)

True for round trip fares, false for one-way fares.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/fareLineItemsBasic/{TripDate}/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}/{RoundTrip}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie } from 'ws-dottie';
import { fetchFareLineItemsBasic } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-fares/core';

  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-16",
    "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 10,
    "RoundTrip": false
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

fare-totals

Calculated fare totals for WSF journeys by selected line items and quantities.

Calculate fare totals for a terminal combination with selected line items and quantities.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (FetchFareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputTripDateParam)

Trip date in YYYY-MM-DD format. Must be within valid date range.

DepartingTerminalID
required
number (FetchFareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the departing terminal.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (FetchFareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Numeric ID of the arriving terminal.

RoundTrip
required
boolean (FetchFareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputRoundTripParam)

True for round trip totals, false for one-way totals.

FareLineItemID
required
string (FetchFareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputFareLineItemIDParam)

Comma-separated list of fare line item IDs (e.g., '1,2,3').

Quantity
required
string (FetchFareTotalsByTripDateAndRouteInputQuantityParam)

Comma-separated list of quantities matching FareLineItemID order (e.g., '2,1,0'). Values must be >= 0.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/fares/rest/fareTotals/{TripDate}/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}/{RoundTrip}/{FareLineItemID}/{Quantity}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie } from 'ws-dottie';
import { fetchFareTotalsByTripDateAndRoute } from 'ws-dottie/wsf-fares/core';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: fetchFareTotalsByTripDateAndRoute,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-15",
    "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 10,
    "RoundTrip": false,
    "FareLineItemID": "1,2",
    "Quantity": "3,1"
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 3 total)

[
  • {
    • "TotalType": 1,
    • "Description": "Anacortes to Friday Harbor",
    • "BriefDescription": "Depart",
    • "Amount": 61.25
    }
